    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20,
                                    1896</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 804.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 755, of the 2d
                            instant, touching the situation in the province of Aleppo.</p>
                <p>The Department heartily approves your purpose to ask to have regular
                            troops detailed for the protection of American citizens at Aintab, and I
                            observe with no slight degree of satisfaction your strong commendation
                            of the action of Mr. Frederick Poche, our consular agent at Aleppo, in
                            behalf of our citizens there. It is most cordially appreciated by the
                            Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
